column2: Counts for deaths where X30 (hyperthermia) was indicated as the underlying (immediate) cause of death.

Counts for deaths where ICD-10 Codes X30 (exposure to excessive natural heat), P81.0 (environmental hyperthermia of newborn), or T67 (effects of heat and light) are listed as the underlying (immediate) cause of death, or as one of the contributing causes of death. Excludes records with ICD-10 code W92 (exposure to excessive heat of man-made origin) listed anywhere on the death certificate to restrict the selection to deaths resulting from natural heat exposure.
